----------------------------------------------------------------------
GLOBAL IGNORES
These apply to all Node.js and React projects
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Dependencies
All Node dependencies folders (usually one for the backend and one for the frontend)
node_modules

Yarn and npm lock files
package-lock.json
yarn.lock

Logs and Debugging
npm-debug.log*
.nyc_output/
coverage/
*.lcov
.DS_Store # Mac operating system files

----------------------------------------------------------------------
BACKEND (Node.js/Express) IGNORES
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Environment Variables
Crucial for security: never commit your sensitive keys
.env
.env.*
.env.local

Database/Storage
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-journal

Compiled/Dist files (if running TypeScript or Babel on the server)
/dist
/build
/output

----------------------------------------------------------------------
FRONTEND (React) IGNORES
Assuming typical setup where the frontend is inside a subdirectory
----------------------------------------------------------------------
Production build files
Files created when you run 'npm run build' or 'yarn build'
/client/build
/frontend/build
/dist
.cache
.parcel-cache

Development servers
.next/ # For Next.js projects
.vercel/ # For Vercel deployment
.nuxt/ # For Nuxt.js projects

Source map files
*.map